## Code Style Guidelines

### General Formatting
- Use 2 spaces for indentation (no tabs)
- Always use semicolons for consistency
- Place opening braces on the same line as the statement
- Maintain consistent spacing around operators
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for class names and components

### Naming Conventions
- Variables: lowerCamelCase
- Functions: lowerCamelCase  
- Classes: PascalCase
- Constants: UPPER_CASE
- Files: kebab-case
- Directories: kebab-case

### Code Structure
- Separate logical sections with blank lines
- Keep functions small and focused (max 50 lines)
- Use meaningful, descriptive names
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3 levels)
- Import statements organized in groups:
  1. Built-in modules
  2. External libraries  
  3. Local modules

### Configuration Management
- ALL numeric values in configuration files must be justified with:
  - Load testing evidence or performance data
  - Risk assessment documentation
  - Rollback plan for production issues
- Critical configuration parameters should have feature flags for gradual rollouts
- Configuration validation should be implemented to prevent invalid settings
- Environment-specific values should be managed through secure, version-controlled configurations

### Comments and Documentation
- Add JSDoc-style comments for functions with parameters
- Comment complex logic
- Remove commented-out code before commit
- Keep comments up to date with code changes